Comparable--> class String implements Comparable{
}
-compareTO() return int value its return type is int
return integer 
positive if greater , negetive if smaller , 0 if equal

example: "2" compareTo("k")

*all wrapper classes has internally implemented comparable interface*

sortedMap specific methods - 

1) firstKey()
Returns the smallest (first) key in the map.

2) lastKey()
Returns the largest (last) key in the map.

3) headMap(K toKey)
Ret	urns entries with keys less than toKey

4) tailMap(K fromKey)
Returns entries with keys greater than or equal to fromKey.

5) tailMap(K fromKey)
Returns entries with keys greater than or equal to fromKey.

6) subMap(K fromKey, K toKey)
Returns entries with keys from fromKey (inclusive) to toKey (exclusive).


=============================================================================================================

Navigable Map specific methods
1) lowerKey(K key)
Greatest key strictly less than given key

2) floorKey(K key)
Greatest key less than or equal to given key

3) ceilingEntry(K key)
Entry with key ≥ given key

4) higherEntry(K key)
Entry with key just above given key

5) pollFirstEntry()	
Removes and returns first (lowest) entry

6)pollLastEntry()		
Removes and returns last (highest) entry

7)descendingMap()	
Returns map in reverse order

8)navigableKeySet()	
Returns keys as a NavigableSet

9)descendingKeySet()	
Returns keys in reverse order

10) headMap(K toKey, boolean inclusive)	
Keys less than (or equal) to given key

11)tailMap(K fromKey, boolean inclusive)		
Keys greater than (or equal) to given key
Arrays utility class 
1) sort() 
Sort array

2) binarySearch()
Search element

3) fill()
Fill with value

4) copyOf()
Copy array

5) copyOfRange()
Copy sub-array

